Package edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design

Class Module

java.lang.Object
edu.byu.ece.rapidSmith.design.Module
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Module extends Object implements Serializable
This class represents the modules as found in XDL. They are used to describe hard macros and RPMs and instances of each.
Author:
Chris Lavin Created on: Jun 22, 2010

    • removeInstance

      public boolean removeInstance(String name)
      This method carefully removes an instance in a design with its pins and possibly nets. Nets are only removed if they are empty after removal of the instance's pins. This method CANNOT remove instances that are part of a ModuleInstance.
      Parameters:
      name - The instance name in the module to remove.
      Returns:
      True if the operation was successful, false otherwise.

    • removeInstance

      Parameters:
      instance - The instance in the design to remove.
      Returns:
      True if the operation was successful, false otherwise.

    • getCorrespondingTile

      public Tile getCorrespondingTile(Tile templateTile, Tile newAnchorTile, Device dev)
      This method will calculate and return the corresponding tile of a module for a new anchor location.
      Parameters:
      templateTile - The tile in the module which acts as a template.
      newAnchorTile - This is the tile of the new anchor instance of the module.
      dev - The device which corresponds to this module.
      Returns:
      The new tile of the module instance which corresponds to the templateTile, or null if none exists.
